==English==
===Etymology===
Named after Anna Bishop, wife of [[w:Henry Bishop|Henry Bishop]] composer of the song ''[[w:Home! Sweet Home!|Home! Sweet Home!]]''.  (Reference: Bill Wannan, ''Australian Folklore'', Lansdowne Press, 1970, reprint 1979 ISBN 0-7018-1309-1, entry for "Madame Bishop", page 359.)
===Noun===
'''[[madame|Madame]] [[Bishop]]'''
# {{AU}} {{slang}} {{obsolete}} A drink comprising [[port]], [[sugar]] and [[nutmeg]].
